# Combinators: `join!` & `select!`

## `join!` — all futures complete

```rust
let (a, b) = tokio::join!(task1(), task2());
```

## `select!` — first future wins

```rust
tokio::select! {
    result = fast_task() => println!("Fast: {result}"),
    result = slow_task() => println!("Slow: {result}"),
}
```

> **Note:** `select!` cancels the other futures when one completes.
